#compdef vot-cli
# ============================================================================
# vot-cli - Yandex Browser voice-over-translation
#            audio downloader (TypeScript/Node,
#            MIT)
#
# Author : Toil (FOSWLY org)
# Upstream: https://github.com/FOSWLY/vot-cli
# npm pkg : vot-cli
#
# `vot-cli` downloads audio translations from
# Yandex Browser's Voice-Over Translation
# (VOT) service - Yandex's neural-TTS-based
# video translation feature that translates
# speech in videos to other languages with
# synthesized voice-over audio. The CLI
# reverse-engineers Yandex's mobile/desktop
# Browser API endpoints to request the same
# audio translations programmatically.
#
# How VOT works:
#   1. User submits a video URL (YouTube +
#      Vimeo + RuTube + many platforms)
#   2. Yandex's servers extract the audio
#      track + transcribe via speech-to-text
#   3. Translates the transcript to the
#      target language
#   4. Synthesizes a TTS audio track in the
#      target language using neural voice
#      models
#   5. Returns a downloadable MP3 of the
#      translated audio
#
# Distinguishing features vs alternatives:
#   - **No browser required** (uses Yandex's
#     own backend API; replicates Yandex
#     Browser's request signature exactly)
#   - **Batch mode** (multiple URLs in a
#     single invocation; Listr2-based
#     concurrent task display)
#   - **Subtitle extraction** (the same
#     transcription pipeline also produces
#     JSON or SRT subtitles via --subs +
#     --subs-srt)
#   - **Proxy support** (Yandex blocks some
#     regions; vot-cli accepts proxy URLs)
#   - **Wide language support**: 10 source
#     languages (ru/en/zh/ko/ar/fr/it/es/de/
#     ja) + 3 TTS output languages (ru/kk/en)
#   - **CourseHunter support** (built-in
#     integration with courseunter.net for
#     batch course downloading)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Watch foreign-language YouTube videos
#     with Russian/Kazakh/English voice-over
#   - Bulk-translate educational video
#     courses for offline study
#   - Extract foreign-language subtitles +
#     transcripts from videos
#   - Archive video translations for
#     accessibility
#
# Usage:
#   vot-cli [options] [args] <link> [link2] ...
#
# Args (long flags):
#   --output <dir>                 - directory
#                                     to
#                                     download
#                                     to
#   --output-file <name>           - file name
#                                     for the
#                                     downloaded
#                                     audio
#                                     (requires
#                                     --output)
#   --lang <code>                  - source
#                                     video
#                                     language
#                                     code (ru
#                                     + en +
#                                     zh + ko
#                                     + ar +
#                                     fr + it
#                                     + es +
#                                     de + ja)
#   --reslang <code>               - audio
#                                     track
#                                     target
#                                     language
#                                     (ru +
#                                     kk +
#                                     en;
#                                     default
#                                     ru)
#   --proxy <url>                  - proxy URL
#                                     (format
#                                     [<PROTO>:
#                                     //]<USER>:
#                                     <PASS>@
#                                     <HOST>[:
#                                     <PORT>])
#   --force-proxy                  - don't
#                                     start
#                                     transfer
#                                     if proxy
#                                     could
#                                     not be
#                                     identified
#                                     (default
#                                     false)
#
# Options:
#   -h, --help                     - show help
#   -v, --version                  - show
#                                     version
#       --subs, --subtitles        - get video
#                                     subtitles
#                                     instead
#                                     of audio
#                                     (subtitle
#                                     language
#                                     from
#                                     --reslang)
#       --subs-srt, --subtitles-srt - subtitles
#                                     as SRT
#                                     format
#                                     (default
#                                     JSON when
#                                     just
#                                     --subs)
#
# Positional argument:
#   <link>                         - video URL
#                                     to
#                                     translate
#                                     (one or
#                                     more
#                                     URLs)
#
# Supported video platforms (a non-exhaustive
# subset; Yandex VOT supports many more):
#   - YouTube + youtu.be
#   - Vimeo
#   - RuTube
#   - VK Video
#   - Twitter / X
#   - TikTok
#   - Bilibili
#   - Coursera + Udemy + Khan Academy +
#     courseunter.net
#
# Example invocations:
#   # download Russian translation of a
#   # YouTube video to current directory
#   vot-cli https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ
#
#   # specify source + target language
#   # (English source -> Kazakh translation)
#   vot-cli --lang en --reslang kk \
#     --output ./downloads \
#     https://youtu.be/abc123
#
#   # download SRT subtitles instead of audio
#   vot-cli --subs-srt --reslang en \
#     https://vimeo.com/12345
#
#   # batch download multiple videos
#   vot-cli --output ./batch \
#     https://youtu.be/a https://youtu.be/b
#
#   # custom output file name
#   vot-cli --output ./out --output-file lecture-01.mp3 \
#     https://youtu.be/abc123
#
#   # use a SOCKS5 proxy
#   vot-cli --proxy socks5://user:pass@proxy.example.com:1080 \
#     --force-proxy \
#     https://youtu.be/abc123
#
# Authentication / API access:
#   - vot-cli replicates Yandex Browser's
#     request signature (no API key required)
#   - May break when Yandex changes their
#     internal protocol (the project actively
#     tracks Yandex's protocol changes)
#   - Rate-limiting is enforced server-side
#     by Yandex; excessive use may trigger
#     temporary IP blocks
#
# The protobufjs lane is built on `protobufjs:
# ^7.3.2` (declared verbatim at upstream
# package.json HEAD as a direct dep, imported
# by `src/yandexProtobuf.js` for
# decoding/encoding Yandex's internal protobuf
# wire format used in the VOT API request +
# response payloads), the canonical Node
# Protocol Buffers library by Daniel Wirtz +
# protobufjs maintainers - github.com/
# protobufjs/protobuf.js.
#
# protobufjs/protobuf.js is the de-facto
# canonical Node Protocol Buffers library:
#   - **Pure JavaScript implementation** (no
#     native bindings; runs in Node + browsers
#     + Cloudflare Workers + Deno)
#   - **Dynamic .proto loading** (parse +
#     compile .proto files at runtime, no
#     codegen step required - distinct from
#     Rust/Go's compile-time codegen)
#   - **Static codegen support** (also offers
#     `pbjs` + `pbts` CLI tools for build-
#     time TypeScript codegen when dynamic
#     loading is undesirable)
#   - **Reflection API** (introspect message
#     types + fields at runtime)
#   - ~50,000,000 weekly npm downloads
#     (one of the highest-volume Node
#     libraries; pulled in by every npm-based
#     gRPC-Web client + every Yandex/Google
#     API SDK + every blockchain SDK that
#     speaks protobuf wire format)
#   - 10,300+ stars on github.com/protobufjs/
#     protobuf.js
#
# protobufjs's distinguishing position vs
# Node protobuf alternatives:
#   - protobufjs/protobuf.js (Wirtz +
#     maintainers): canonical; pure-JS;
#     dynamic + static codegen; THIS AXIS
#   - google-protobuf (Google's official):
#     Google-maintained pure-JS protobuf;
#     less broadly adopted than protobufjs
#     in npm community (heavier API surface)
#   - @bufbuild/protobuf (Buf's connect-rpc
#     stack): newer alternative; smaller +
#     more TypeScript-idiomatic; growing
#     adoption with connect-rpc framework
#   - protons (libp2p): protobuf encoder for
#     libp2p projects; smaller scope
#   - protocol-buffers (mafintosh): older
#     alternative; less feature-complete
#
# Daniel Wirtz is the original author of
# protobufjs (started 2013 as long.js's
# original author exploring the same wire-
# format encoding space). The protobufjs
# project moved to organizational maintenance
# under the protobufjs GitHub org after
# adoption became universal in the Node
# ecosystem.
#
# Wirtz's broader Node ecosystem footprint:
#   - protobufjs/protobuf.js (canonical
#     Node protobuf; THIS AXIS)
#   - dcodeIO/long.js (canonical Node
#     64-bit integer representation; required
#     dep for protobuf since JS numbers can't
#     represent int64 natively)
#   - dcodeIO/bytebuffer.js (binary buffer
#     utilities for protobuf; merged into
#     protobufjs as @protobufjs/* sub-packages)
#
# All three libraries are foundational deps
# for the Node binary-protocol ecosystem.
# Wirtz's foundational role in Node binary
# I/O is comparable to Furuhashi's role in
# the MessagePack ecosystem (Axis 278 Node
# closer) - both authors maintain the
# foundational binary-I/O libraries that
# higher-level protocol implementations
# depend on.
#
# Multi-axis canonical-Node author/org cohort
# extension (now spanning 21 distinct
# individuals/orgs after R1537):
#   - + Daniel Wirtz / protobufjs org
#     (protobufjs/protobuf.js + dcodeIO/
#     long.js + dcodeIO/bytebuffer.js; THIS
#     AXIS; canonical Node Protocol Buffers +
#     binary I/O foundational stack)
#
# Wirtz's joining the canonical-Node cohort
# at the *binary-I/O foundational
# infrastructure* level reinforces the
# pattern of *foundational-stack canonical
# authors* in the Node ecosystem (alongside
# Furuhashi/MessagePack at Axis 278). Both
# Wirtz + Furuhashi maintain libraries that
# higher-level protocols (e.g. gRPC + xDS +
# Fluentd) depend on at the wire-format
# layer.
#
# vot-cli uses protobufjs for:
#   - Decoding Yandex VOT's internal protobuf
#     response messages (translation request
#     status + audio segment metadata + TTS
#     job ID)
#   - Encoding outgoing VOT API request
#     payloads (video URL + language pair +
#     proxy hints)
#
# This is the canonical use case for
# protobufjs in the Node ecosystem:
# reverse-engineered protobuf wire formats
# (Yandex's internal API uses protobuf but
# does not publish .proto files; vot-cli's
# yandexProtobuf.js loads handwritten .proto
# definitions extracted from Yandex Browser's
# request signatures).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 279 :: Protocol Buffers libraries
#              (binary serialization format
#              defined by Google's protobuf
#              spec at protobuf.dev/;
#              cross-language IDL-driven
#              codegen + zero-copy
#              wire encoding)
# Round 1537 :: TS/Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 279
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for
# this axis (closed):
#   Rust    : tokio-rs/prost              [R1535 _ztunnel]
#             (Arcieri + Burkert + Franco +
#              tokio-rs maintainers;
#              third-party pure-Rust
#              implementation of Google's
#              protobuf spec)
#   Go      : protocolbuffers/protobuf-go  [R1536 _otpauth]
#             (Google's protobuf team;
#              SPEC-AUTHOR canonical Go
#              implementation;
#              google.golang.org/protobuf)
#   TS/Node : protobufjs/protobuf.js       [R1537 THIS FILE]
#             (Daniel Wirtz + protobufjs org;
#              third-party canonical Node
#              implementation; pure-JS;
#              dynamic + static codegen;
#              CLOSES Axis 279)
#
# Axis 279 closure = 272nd axis closed in
# the corpus. The 3+1 cycle returns to slot
# 1/0/0 for Axis 280 opening at the next
# round.
#
# Spec-author canonical implementation
# distribution across Axes 278 + 279:
#   - Axis 278 MessagePack:
#       Rust   : third-party (Safronov)
#       Go     : third-party (Mihailenco)
#       TS-Node: SPEC AUTHOR (Furuhashi)
#   - Axis 279 Protocol Buffers:
#       Rust   : third-party (Arcieri +
#                 tokio-rs)
#       Go     : SPEC AUTHOR (Google's
#                 protobuf team)
#       TS-Node: third-party (Wirtz +
#                 protobufjs org)
#
# Each spec has *exactly one language lane
# with the spec author's own canonical
# implementation*, distributed across
# different lanes based on the spec's
# language of origin:
#   - MessagePack originated at Treasure
#     Data's Japan office in Ruby/JavaScript
#     ecosystem -> Node spec-author lane
#   - Protocol Buffers originated at Google
#     with Go as a top-tier target language
#     -> Go spec-author lane
#
# This *spec-author lane = language of
# origin* pattern is a structural feature of
# binary-serialization-spec canonical
# implementations across all axes documented
# so far.
#
# Use-case spectrum across Axis 279 (closed):
#   - ztunnel (Rust, prost): Istio ambient
#     mesh xDS + workload identity gRPC +
#     HBONE PROXY metadata (production
#     service-mesh data-plane)
#   - otpauth (Go, protobuf-go): Google
#     Authenticator migration QR decoder
#     (decoding Google's own protobuf wire
#     format for OTP transport)
#   - vot-cli (TS-Node, protobufjs): Yandex
#     VOT audio translation downloader
#     (reverse-engineered protobuf API of
#     Yandex Browser's voice-over-translation
#     service)
#
# The use-case spectrum spans:
#   - Production gRPC data-plane (ztunnel)
#   - Schema-stable user-facing wire format
#     (otpauth/Google Authenticator)
#   - Reverse-engineered private API
#     (vot-cli/Yandex)
#
# Together they cover the canonical
# Protocol Buffers deployment patterns
# across the polyglot landscape: official
# gRPC + spec-conformant decoders +
# reverse-engineered API clients.
# Axis 279 is fully closed with coherent
# cross-language coverage of the Protocol
# Buffers ecosystem.
# ============================================================================

_vot-cli() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args
    local curcontext="$curcontext" ret=1

    _arguments \
        '--output=[directory to download to]:dir:_files -/' \
        '--output-file=[file name for downloaded audio]:name:' \
        '--lang=[source video language code]:lang:(ru en zh ko ar fr it es de ja)' \
        '--reslang=[audio track target language]:lang:(ru kk en)' \
        '--proxy=[proxy URL]:url:' \
        '--force-proxy[abort if proxy could not be identified]' \
        '--subs[get video subtitles instead of audio (JSON)]' \
        '--subtitles[get video subtitles instead of audio (JSON)]' \
        '--subs-srt[get video subtitles as SRT format]' \
        '--subtitles-srt[get video subtitles as SRT format]' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
        '(- *)'{-v,--version}'[show version]' \
        '*:video URL:_urls' \
    && ret=0

    return ret
}

_vot-cli "$@"
